      "milestone": "Final Project C1",
      "details": {
        "incident_summary": "Input integrity counter `iris_input_anomalies_total` was not registering NaN events because the traffic generator's JSON encoder rejected NaN values before transmission.",
        "detection": "Prometheus query `iris_input_anomalies_total{anomaly_type='nan'}` returned empty during dashboard build of Panel 5.",
        "root_cause": "`requests.post(json=payload)` uses strict JSON which raises ValueError on NaN floats.",
        "resolution": "Switched traffic_gen.py to `json.dumps(payload, allow_nan=True)` and explicit Content-Type header, restoring NaN test coverage.",
        "files_changed": ["src/monitoring/traffic_gen.py"],
        "follow_up": "Documented in dashboard-interpretation.md as a real-world example of upstream serialization issues that input integrity monitoring is designed to catch."
      }
    },
